Package org.tms.api.io

Options to import and export Tables to a variety of formats.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ArchivalIOOption<T extends ArchivalIOOption<T>>
    An IOOption where the output can persist TMS-specific functionality.
    DateTimeFormatIOOption<T extends DateTimeFormatIOOption<T>>
    A IOOption where the output can have a date-time displayed in the output footer.
    IOOption<T extends IOOption<T>>
    The base for all IOOption, which facilitate the import and export of Tables to other file formats.
    PageableIOOption<T extends PageableIOOption<T>>
    An IOOption where the output can be paged.
    StyleableIOOption<T extends StyleableIOOption<T>>
    An IOOption where the output can be Styled.
    TitleableIOOption<T extends TitleableIOOption<T>>
    An IOOption where the output can be titled.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CSVOptions
    CSVOptions is a concrete class for representing configuration options to import and export comma-separated values (CSV) data.
    DOCOptions
    DocOptions is a concrete class for representing configuration options to export Tables in MS Word format.
    HTMLOptions
    HTMLOptions is a concrete class for representing configuration options to export Tables in HTML format.
    PDFOptions
    PDFOptions is a concrete class for representing configuration options to export Tables in PDF format.
    RTFOptions
    RTFOptions is a concrete class for representing configuration options to export Tables in Rich Text (RTF) format.
    TCOptions  
    TMSOptions  
    XLSOptions
    XLSOptions is a concrete class for representing configuration options to import and export Tables from/to MS Excel in xlsx or xls format.
    XMLOptions  
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    IOFileFormat
    The external file formats that TMS Tables can be exported to and, in some cases, imported from.
